Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION urging the Legislative Council
2 to assign the topic of mobile driving credentials to the
3 appropriate study committee.
4 Whereas, Digital driving credentials (or mobile driver's
5 licenses - mDLs) are offered to modernize identification (ID) by
6 replacing or supplementing physical cards with secure, digital,
7 and instantly verifiable versions on smartphones;
8 Whereas, mDLs are cryptographically signed, making them
9 much harder to forge than physical cards, supporting real-time
10 revocation if a device is stolen and biometric authentication to
11 prevent unauthorized access;
12 Whereas, Unlike a physical ID, which reveals personal
13 details at once, mDLs allow users to share only the necessary
14 information;
15 Whereas, mDLs allow for contactless, fast verification and
16 are Transportation Safety Administration approved;
17 Whereas, mDLs reduce the risks of identity theft and
18 provide a more secure method to conduct business;
2026 DR 3855/DI aj

2
1 Whereas, Offering mDLs provides significant cost savings
2 by eliminating the expenses associated with physical card
3 production, reducing labor-intensive administrative tasks, and
4 minimizing fraud; and
5 Whereas, Twenty states offer digital driving credentials:
6 Therefore,
7
8 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
9 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
10
11 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate urges the Legislative
12 Council to assign the topic of mobile driving credentials to the
13 appropriate study committee.
14
15 SECTION 2. That the Secretary of the Senate is directed to
16 transmit copies of this Resolution to State Senator J.D. Ford.
